title: @OspreyMGolf Climbs Two Spots in 2nd Round of Tavistock Collegiate
text: @OspreyMGolf Climbs Two Spots in 2nd Round of Tavistock Collegiate Story Links Round 2 Results (pdf) WINDERMERE, Fla . -- Battling blustery conditions, the No. 60-ranked North Florida men's golf team shot a second round 293 and moved up two spots to fourth place Monday in competitive field at the Tavistock Collegiate Invitational held at Isleworth Country Club (par 72 / 7,544 yards).The Ospreys, who own a two-round total of 583, climbed from a tie for sixth into the Top 5 after posting a 5-over total. Senior Andrew Alligood sparked the charge for UNF as both players finished with 1-under-par 71. For Alligood, the scored marked the lowest of his collegiate career and was also his first under-par score. Hancock and Alligood each head into Tuesday's final round tied for seventh in the medalist rankings at even-par 144.Senior Travis Trace rounds out the Osprey lineup in a tie for 55th at 153."The team got off to a really fast start today making the turn at 5-under," said head coach Scott Schroeder . "Unfortunately the wind picked up on the back nine and we struggled a bit down the stretch. It was a great learning experience for our team. We have played alongside the number one team in the country thru two rounds and have been very competitive. We are looking forward to another challenging day in the final round."No. 15 California continues to lead the team competition with a 36-hole tally of 569 (-7). No. 3 Illinois is second at 578 followed by No. 10 Arizona State (579), UNF and No. 17 Vanderbilt (584) rounding out the Top 5 squads. Cal's Collin Morikawa (137) owns a one shot advantage on the field in the medalist standings.Tournament action at the Tavistock Collegiate concludes Tuesday with a final round of 18 holes. North Florida will play alongside Vanderbilt and North Carolina on the last day beginning at 8:50 a.m. on Hole 1. Live scoring for the event is available online at Golfstat.com.
